docs.abstract: The new course will undergo a pilot program in 60 schools, as the debate over how to teach history becomes ever more divisive.
docs.snippet: The new course will undergo a pilot program in 60 schools, as the debate over how to teach history becomes ever more divisive.
docs.lead_paragraph: The College Board is jumping into the fray over how to teach the history of race in the United States with a new Advanced Placement course and exam on African American studies that will be tried out in about 60 high schools this fall.

headline.main: The First A.P. African American Studies Class Is Coming This Fall
headline.print_headline: The First A.P. Course On African Americans Is Offered in the Fall

docs.abstract: Catholicism is the new hip thing, partly as a rejection of progressive morality, partly as an aesthetic posture among the fashionable New Right.
docs.snippet: Catholicism is the new hip thing, partly as a rejection of progressive morality, partly as an aesthetic posture among the fashionable New Right.
docs.lead_paragraph: As senior churchmen seek to make Catholicism palatable to modernity, members of a small but significant scene are turning to the ancient faith in defiance of liberal pieties. The scene is often associated with “Dimes Square,” a downtown Manhattan neighborhood popular with a pandemic-weary Generation Z — or Zoomer — crowd, but it has spread across a network of podcasts and upstart publications. Its sensibility is more transgressive than progressive. Many of its denizens profess to be apolitical. Others hold outré opinions, whether sincerely or as fashion statements. Reactionary motifs are chic: Trump hats and “tradwife” frocks, monarchist and anti-feminist sentiments. Perhaps the ultimate expression of this contrarian aesthetic is its embrace of Catholicism.

headline.main: New York’s Hottest Club Is the Catholic Church
headline.print_headline: New York’s Hottest Club Is the Catholic Church

docs.abstract: Nurse, 27, is the first Black woman to win Olympic gold in women’s hockey. Before she set the single-tournament points record in Beijing, she faced years of underestimation.
docs.snippet: Nurse, 27, is the first Black woman to win Olympic gold in women’s hockey. Before she set the single-tournament points record in Beijing, she faced years of underestimation.
docs.lead_paragraph: TORONTO — Not even six years ago — before Sarah Nurse’s Olympic medals, before the Olympic record she set, before the Cheerios boxes and Barbie dolls bearing her image — Canada was content to leave her off its national women’s hockey team.

headline.main: In Sarah Nurse, a Found Voice for Hockey
headline.print_headline: First She Asserted Herself on the Ice, Then in the World

docs.abstract: Presented with two stalwarts of the status quo, many are opting out.
docs.snippet: Presented with two stalwarts of the status quo, many are opting out.
docs.lead_paragraph: NAIROBI, Kenya — It was a sight to behold. Scores of young people, excited and expectant, gathered in Nairobi, chanting slogans and waving banners. But it was no entertainment: They were there for a campaign rally. In the months leading up to Kenya’s elections on Tuesday, the scene was repeated across the country. Here, it seemed, were the future custodians of the country taking a lively interest in the political process.

headline.main: Young Kenyans Are Being Asked to Crown Their New Oppressor, and the Answer Is No

docs.abstract: The police in Louisville, Ky., fatally shot Ms. Taylor during a nighttime raid on her apartment. Prosecutors said officers had lied in order to obtain a search warrant for Ms. Taylor’s home.
docs.snippet: The police in Louisville, Ky., fatally shot Ms. Taylor during a nighttime raid on her apartment. Prosecutors said officers had lied in order to obtain a search warrant for Ms. Taylor’s home.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than two years after police officers killed Breonna Taylor during a late-night raid of her apartment in Louisville, Ky., the Justice Department announced a series of federal charges on Thursday against four of the officers involved in the operation that set off racial justice protests across the country.

headline.main: Federal Officials Charge Four Officers in Breonna Taylor Raid
headline.print_headline: 4 Officers Face Federal Charges In Taylor Killing
